  "text": "The regenerative potential of skeletal muscle is dependent on the interaction between skeletal muscle and immune cells. In response to injury, immune cells infiltrate skeletal muscle in order to restore muscle homeostasis by removing necrotic cells and secreting growth factors necessary for satellite cell proliferation and differentiation [CITATION_1] . The physiological functions of immune cells are gradually lost with advanced age leading to impaired regenerative capacity of skeletal muscle [CITATION_2] .",
